# Regressions {.tabset}

We present regressions of the type: $$
   \Delta^k\mathrm{ILSBEI}_t(n) = \alpha_n + \beta_n \times \Delta^k\mathrm{CDS}_t+\varepsilon_t(n)\,,
$$ where $n$ is the maturity, and $CDS_t$ is the level of the
EUR-denominated CDS We estimate this regression for $k\in\{0,1\}$, i.e.
level-level and diff-diff. All standard deviations are computed with
Newey-West using an automatically selected number of lags.

